1
00:00:05,731 --> 00:00:07,401
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,461 --> 00:00:09,101
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:09,601 --> 00:00:11,531
What's all this? You shouldn't have.

4
00:00:11,871 --> 00:00:13,471
It's some fresh cabbage kimchi.

5
00:00:13,971 --> 00:00:16,771
It's nice and crunchy. It's so good!

6
00:00:16,871 --> 00:00:19,681
Goodness, but you already brought me
the braised beans...

7
00:00:19,741 --> 00:00:22,281
and a ton of stir-fried anchovies.

8
00:00:22,851 --> 00:00:25,111
- Hello, ma'am!
- Right.

9
00:00:25,651 --> 00:00:29,521
Yes, you shouldn't bend your knees
too much.

10
00:00:29,721 --> 00:00:31,921
Yes, keep them straight like this
whenever possible.

11
00:00:31,921 --> 00:00:35,161
Okay, let's focus on the infrared
and manual therapy...

12
00:00:35,161 --> 00:00:36,231
I'm here.

13
00:00:36,391 --> 00:00:38,701
Does it hurt a lot when I do this?
I'm going to lift it one more time.

14
00:00:38,761 --> 00:00:40,061
- How about when I do this?
- Yes.

15
00:00:40,131 --> 00:00:41,501
At this point,
I think she needs manual therapy.

16
00:00:41,501 --> 00:00:42,701
All right,
go ahead and lower it. Yes.

17
00:00:43,601 --> 00:00:46,241
Try to lift it up one more time.
No, slowly.

18
00:00:46,301 --> 00:00:47,701
Just use your own strength. Yes.

19
00:00:50,141 --> 00:00:51,741
Leave it. I want to watch this.

20
00:00:51,941 --> 00:00:54,981
Do you really think this is the time
to be lazing around watching TV?

21
00:00:55,581 --> 00:00:57,181
Come on, turn it on. Let me watch.

22
00:00:57,651 --> 00:01:01,051
Get to work!
The cost of moving because of you...

23
00:01:01,251 --> 00:01:02,491
That's not just a few bucks,
you know.

24
00:01:02,851 --> 00:01:05,391
Look, I get it, okay?
Now, turn it on.

25
00:01:05,391 --> 00:01:07,121
My goodness.
Seriously, what is with you?

26
00:01:07,291 --> 00:01:11,491
Because this place looks familiar.
And the people look familiar too.

27
00:01:11,731 --> 00:01:13,001
There's no way.

28
00:01:13,201 --> 00:01:17,471
Let go.
I'm about to remember something.

29
00:01:20,801 --> 00:01:22,541
Why are you being like this again?

30
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:26,211
- Let go of me! Let go!
- Please, just stop.

31
00:01:29,411 --> 00:01:31,511
- Gosh, my meds...
- Gi Cheol.

32
00:01:31,711 --> 00:01:35,151
- Get me my meds.
- Okay, hold on.

33
00:01:40,361 --> 00:01:41,661
I like the outfits.

34
00:01:41,891 --> 00:01:44,161
("Human Theater")

35
00:01:45,761 --> 00:01:48,431
- Here, have some.
- I want some too!

36
00:01:48,731 --> 00:01:49,731
Eat your own.

37
00:01:49,801 --> 00:01:53,241
I wonder if our mom
is watching this too.

38
00:01:54,501 --> 00:01:55,511
She probably is.

39
00:01:57,241 --> 00:01:58,941
Your mom might be watching too.

40
00:01:59,211 --> 00:02:02,511
- Right?
- If she is, what would she think?

41
00:02:03,611 --> 00:02:06,851
She'd probably be relieved
that we're doing well.

42
00:02:08,251 --> 00:02:10,451
I called my dad
and told him to watch it.

43
00:02:10,951 --> 00:02:12,161
What for?

44
00:02:13,021 --> 00:02:16,461
So he can get a good, hard look
at the happiness he threw away.

45
00:02:18,131 --> 00:02:19,531
Do you think he would've left
if he knew?

46
00:02:21,001 --> 00:02:25,401
People who abandon their kids
should get what's coming to them.

47
00:02:26,141 --> 00:02:28,911
But maybe it's because
it's been so long.

48
00:02:29,541 --> 00:02:31,311
I'm not mad at our mom anymore.

49
00:02:31,971 --> 00:02:33,911
Sometimes, I even miss her.

50
00:02:34,681 --> 00:02:36,951
And I wonder
if she's even still alive.

51
00:02:38,751 --> 00:02:39,821
Don't you feel the same?

52
00:02:40,251 --> 00:02:41,481
My wife too...

53
00:02:49,561 --> 00:02:51,831
(Gu In Ok, went missing at age 43)

54
00:02:53,361 --> 00:02:54,531
Our mom.

55
00:02:55,161 --> 00:02:56,971
I wonder if she really looks
this old now.

56
00:02:59,041 --> 00:03:02,141
Jeong Han and Dae Han made this
with AI, Dad.

57
00:03:03,371 --> 00:03:05,711
They went around Seongdam today
putting them up everywhere.

58
00:03:06,741 --> 00:03:07,741
They did?

59
00:03:07,911 --> 00:03:12,321
I read articles that some have found
missing relatives this way, Father.

60
00:03:15,381 --> 00:03:19,461
Right after, someone said they saw
someone similar, so they went...

61
00:03:20,021 --> 00:03:21,021
Really?

62
00:03:21,661 --> 00:03:23,361
But they said they'd moved,
and the place was empty.

63
00:03:26,201 --> 00:03:28,831
Father, instead of doing this,

64
00:03:28,901 --> 00:03:31,271
why don't you report her as missing
to the police?

65
00:03:32,801 --> 00:03:33,801
Drop it.

66
00:03:34,701 --> 00:03:36,141
They both left
on their own two feet.

67
00:03:36,471 --> 00:03:37,511
How can you call that "missing?"

68
00:03:51,091 --> 00:03:54,691
You don't think he moved on purpose
because he knew we were looking?

69
00:03:55,791 --> 00:03:57,691
There's no way to know.

70
00:03:58,191 --> 00:04:02,061
I checked his official records
just in case,

71
00:04:02,231 --> 00:04:04,971
but he still hasn't registered
a new address.

72
00:04:05,641 --> 00:04:07,471
I don't think we can find him
on our own.

73
00:04:08,071 --> 00:04:12,011
- We should go to the police...
- Forget it. He's hiding so hard.

74
00:04:12,071 --> 00:04:13,511
What's the point of finding him?

75
00:04:14,941 --> 00:04:18,451
Maybe it wasn't Father who moved.

76
00:04:19,221 --> 00:04:20,381
She's right, Mom.

77
00:04:20,851 --> 00:04:24,591
It'd be a shame to give up now,
so I'll go back when I can and...

78
00:04:24,851 --> 00:04:28,091
- check CCTV near the tailor shop...
- Tailor shop?

79
00:04:28,461 --> 00:04:30,761
It looked like
a clothing repair shop.

80
00:04:31,261 --> 00:04:32,301
Why, Mom?

81
00:04:34,001 --> 00:04:35,001
It's nothing.

82
00:04:36,001 --> 00:04:38,901
If he won't come back on his own,
I don't want to track him down.

83
00:04:39,301 --> 00:04:41,901
I just want to focus on Seong Mi,

84
00:04:42,201 --> 00:04:44,511
so let's just drop this, okay?

85
00:05:39,161 --> 00:05:41,261
(Missing Person)

86
00:05:42,731 --> 00:05:44,001
Tailor shop...

87
00:05:45,371 --> 00:05:47,841
Wait, doesn't Mi Hyang run
a tailor shop?

88
00:05:55,041 --> 00:05:58,851
(Missing Person)

89
00:06:02,121 --> 00:06:04,491
The call cannot be connected.
Forwarding to voicemail.

90
00:06:04,591 --> 00:06:06,491
Please leave a message
after the tone...

91
00:06:08,021 --> 00:06:10,161
I mean, her shop isn't the only one.

92
00:06:15,131 --> 00:06:17,431
(Missing Person)

93
00:06:22,041 --> 00:06:25,641
(Luxury Custom Tailoring
and Alterations)

94
00:06:32,951 --> 00:06:35,991
(Luxury Custom Tailoring
and Alterations)

95
00:06:43,061 --> 00:06:46,161
(Clothing Alterations)

96
00:06:49,671 --> 00:06:51,431
(Luxury Custom Tailoring
and Alterations)

97
00:06:53,841 --> 00:06:55,871
(Missing Person)

98
00:06:58,841 --> 00:07:01,741
Gong Gi Cheol...

99
00:07:04,181 --> 00:07:05,351
(Luxury Custom Tailoring
and Alterations)

100
00:07:11,921 --> 00:07:14,321
(Missing Person)

101
00:07:20,201 --> 00:07:21,601
(Missing Person)

102
00:07:23,531 --> 00:07:26,471
I wonder what they're talking about
without us.

103
00:07:26,901 --> 00:07:27,901
Hey.

104
00:07:28,901 --> 00:07:32,581
Why not go hang out with Gong Ju Ah
instead of bugging me?

105
00:07:32,841 --> 00:07:34,611
Gong Ju Ah is
kind of busy, actually.

106
00:07:35,341 --> 00:07:36,411
Figures.

107
00:07:37,751 --> 00:07:40,351
Just eat and stop making that face.

108
00:07:47,421 --> 00:07:49,161
Did our birth mom get remarried?

109
00:07:53,531 --> 00:07:54,531
Yes, she did.

110
00:07:56,971 --> 00:07:58,831
So I guess she's living happily.

111
00:08:00,441 --> 00:08:01,601
She seemed really happy.

112
00:08:04,941 --> 00:08:06,281
Were you really upset?

113
00:08:08,311 --> 00:08:09,311
Yes.

114
00:08:10,081 --> 00:08:11,081
But...

115
00:08:11,651 --> 00:08:15,421
In a way, I was also glad.

116
00:08:16,721 --> 00:08:19,091
If she were living an unhappy life,
missing us,

117
00:08:19,561 --> 00:08:21,121
I think I would've been
even more upset.

118
00:08:27,901 --> 00:08:30,601
Does she have other kids?

119
00:08:32,001 --> 00:08:33,001
Yes.

120
00:08:33,601 --> 00:08:34,801
A girl around your age.

121
00:08:38,941 --> 00:08:41,711
I bet she'd hate it
if I reached out to Mom.

122
00:08:44,511 --> 00:08:45,751
Hard to say.

123
00:08:46,451 --> 00:08:47,851
She might.

124
00:09:01,201 --> 00:09:02,231
Hey, babe.

125
00:09:02,701 --> 00:09:03,801
I can't believe you.

126
00:09:04,031 --> 00:09:05,801
The show ended,
and you didn't even call me.

127
00:09:06,071 --> 00:09:07,101
Are you that busy?

128
00:09:07,471 --> 00:09:10,411
Yes. I have to finish organizing
the concept book today.

129
00:09:10,671 --> 00:09:14,341
- Where are you?
- Home. I just got back from a walk.

130
00:09:14,781 --> 00:09:17,351
By the way, I heard you helped
my mom move her things out today.

131
00:09:18,111 --> 00:09:20,451
Yes. Did Dr. Han tell you?

132
00:09:20,721 --> 00:09:24,021
Yes. Why didn't you tell me?

133
00:09:24,421 --> 00:09:26,691
Are you mad?
Did I do something wrong?

134
00:09:27,061 --> 00:09:28,761
No, I'm saying you did a great job.

135
00:09:29,361 --> 00:09:31,891
How can I praise you for it
if I don't know?

136
00:09:33,001 --> 00:09:36,431
I didn't say anything
because you were busy and stressed.

137
00:09:36,901 --> 00:09:40,141
From now on, tell me everything.
Even the little things.

138
00:09:40,871 --> 00:09:45,211
But telling you everything is weird,
especially when it's not about us.

139
00:09:45,711 --> 00:09:50,311
What do you mean?
Couples shouldn't have secrets.

140
00:09:50,781 --> 00:09:53,851
- Really?
- Yes, really. Why?

141
00:09:54,521 --> 00:09:57,551
You're actually
pretty secretive with me.

142
00:09:57,851 --> 00:10:00,761
I had to find out from Jun Hyeok
that you met my grandma.

143
00:10:01,491 --> 00:10:04,891
Okay, I get it.
No more secrets from now on.

144
00:10:06,431 --> 00:10:07,461
My gosh.

145
00:10:08,001 --> 00:10:11,371
While watching the show today,
I got the biggest surprise.

146
00:10:11,801 --> 00:10:13,801
My heart's still racing.

147
00:10:14,171 --> 00:10:16,241
Why? What happened?

148
00:10:16,571 --> 00:10:18,941
I thought "Human Theater"
was supposed to feature humans,

149
00:10:19,641 --> 00:10:21,341
but all of a sudden,
an angel appeared.

150
00:10:22,781 --> 00:10:24,581
Gosh, I don't know
what you're talking about.

151
00:10:26,121 --> 00:10:30,221
Good. You shouldn't know.
Let me be the only one.

152
00:10:33,191 --> 00:10:36,291
I heard you went to look
for my mom and your dad.

153
00:10:37,131 --> 00:10:38,131
Yes.

154
00:10:40,001 --> 00:10:41,601
And you didn't even tell me.

155
00:10:43,371 --> 00:10:45,971
I just assumed you would've heard
from your brother.

156
00:10:46,541 --> 00:10:48,001
Are you mad I didn't tell you?

157
00:10:48,471 --> 00:10:51,541
No, I'm not mad, but...

158
00:10:53,341 --> 00:10:54,611
What's wrong?

159
00:10:55,741 --> 00:10:57,851
Tell me.
Just tell me everything, come on.

160
00:11:01,581 --> 00:11:03,821
I'm sure something's wrong,

161
00:11:04,291 --> 00:11:05,651
and the reason
you're not telling me...

162
00:11:06,261 --> 00:11:08,421
is because you don't want me
to worry, right?

163
00:11:10,761 --> 00:11:11,761
Yes, that's right.

164
00:11:12,061 --> 00:11:14,101
But if you put yourself in my shoes,

165
00:11:14,631 --> 00:11:17,371
if I were worried about something
and didn't tell you,

166
00:11:18,171 --> 00:11:20,001
how would you feel?

167
00:11:27,781 --> 00:11:28,841
Dong Suk.

168
00:11:32,381 --> 00:11:34,121
My sister-in-law has breast cancer.

169
00:11:42,291 --> 00:11:44,191
Are you okay?

170
00:11:47,201 --> 00:11:49,401
I'm doing better than she is,
I guess.

171
00:11:54,341 --> 00:11:57,571
But she's like a sister to you.

172
00:11:59,541 --> 00:12:01,981
Don't hold back. It's okay to cry.

173
00:12:03,081 --> 00:12:04,081
It's okay.

174
00:12:05,811 --> 00:12:08,621
You really should've told me sooner.

175
00:12:14,361 --> 00:12:15,491
Hey, listen.

176
00:12:18,291 --> 00:12:20,431
I'm going to do everything I can
for my sister-in-law.

177
00:12:20,961 --> 00:12:24,301
But I won't neglect you and me,
so don't you worry, okay?

178
00:12:24,731 --> 00:12:26,601
That's not what I'm worried about...

179
00:12:27,871 --> 00:12:32,541
Let's not go out of our way
to get our families' approval, okay?

180
00:12:33,111 --> 00:12:34,581
I'm telling you. I can do both.

181
00:12:35,611 --> 00:12:37,711
I really want to be your Superman.

182
00:12:37,781 --> 00:12:42,521
I don't love you for being Superman.
I love you for being Gong Dae Han.

183
00:12:49,791 --> 00:12:52,431
What about Woo Jae?
He doesn't know, does he?

184
00:12:53,901 --> 00:12:57,131
Please, keep it a secret from him.

185
00:12:57,901 --> 00:12:59,101
Of course.

186
00:13:01,401 --> 00:13:03,771
He'd be so upset if he found out.

187
00:13:05,511 --> 00:13:07,141
My Woo Jae takes after me.

188
00:13:08,311 --> 00:13:10,281
He's got a soft heart
and cries easily.

189
00:13:26,461 --> 00:13:27,831
What's this?

190
00:13:28,431 --> 00:13:30,771
The "Human Theater" highlights
are already up?

191
00:13:34,641 --> 00:13:37,041
- Hey, leave your brother's stuff.
- Oh, seriously!

192
00:13:37,271 --> 00:13:39,011
That's what you get.

193
00:13:39,071 --> 00:13:41,811
("Human Theater")

194
00:13:44,851 --> 00:13:45,911
What's this?

195
00:13:46,421 --> 00:13:48,121
What the...
What was I doing just now?

196
00:13:50,151 --> 00:13:52,251
Gosh, what is wrong with me?

197
00:14:01,431 --> 00:14:02,761
You're still up?

198
00:14:03,371 --> 00:14:04,771
Yes.

199
00:14:06,031 --> 00:14:09,241
The show your family was on today
got posted on YouTube.

200
00:14:09,401 --> 00:14:12,611
I was showing my American family
and bragging a little.

201
00:14:14,911 --> 00:14:18,311
Watching the show today
really made me miss my family.

202
00:14:19,251 --> 00:14:21,681
Why don't you go back to the US?

203
00:14:22,481 --> 00:14:24,551
Actually,
I've been thinking about it.

204
00:14:25,321 --> 00:14:28,591
I thought if I found my birth mom,
we could spend time together,

205
00:14:28,691 --> 00:14:30,731
which is why
I planned such a long trip.

206
00:14:31,431 --> 00:14:34,501
Hey, if you want to go back
but you're only staying for Ji Hu,

207
00:14:34,561 --> 00:14:36,371
I can talk to them for you.

208
00:14:36,801 --> 00:14:39,941
What if I stay
until after Ji Hu's midterms?

209
00:14:40,341 --> 00:14:43,711
No, you don't need to.
That's harder on you.

210
00:14:43,771 --> 00:14:45,741
Just be selfish for once.

211
00:14:46,141 --> 00:14:49,281
No. It's just that
I want more time with you, too.

212
00:14:49,341 --> 00:14:51,251
And not Woo Jae?

213
00:14:51,951 --> 00:14:56,291
- What?
- Forget it. I'm tired, I'll rest.

214
00:15:14,571 --> 00:15:15,571
What?

215
00:15:16,871 --> 00:15:18,241
Where have you been so late?

216
00:15:18,811 --> 00:15:21,611
I had to take care of something.

217
00:15:21,611 --> 00:15:23,711
Why did you
move your stuff out already?

218
00:15:23,781 --> 00:15:25,781
I told you I'd help you
when I had time.

219
00:15:25,851 --> 00:15:28,951
It's fine. It's better for Dr. Kang
if I get my stuff out quickly.

220
00:15:29,251 --> 00:15:31,721
Come on, it's because
you shouldn't lift heavy things.

221
00:15:33,391 --> 00:15:35,421
Don't tell me
you're actually worried about me.

222
00:15:36,531 --> 00:15:37,991
If something goes wrong
before surgery,

223
00:15:37,991 --> 00:15:40,131
it's harder on the family, okay?

224
00:15:40,631 --> 00:15:43,871
That's more like it. Don't worry.

225
00:15:44,131 --> 00:15:46,501
Director Yang carried them
to my door.

226
00:15:46,741 --> 00:15:47,741
Director Yang?

227
00:15:48,301 --> 00:15:49,911
Wait, not Jun Hyeok?

228
00:15:50,311 --> 00:15:53,311
Ju Ah and Jun Hyeok...
They broke up.

229
00:15:53,841 --> 00:15:55,781
What? Why?

230
00:15:56,351 --> 00:15:59,051
Then why did he come over?
We were starting to like him.

231
00:15:59,111 --> 00:16:03,221
- I know, right?
- Man, I really liked that kid.

232
00:16:03,521 --> 00:16:05,051
It's a real shame.

233
00:16:05,351 --> 00:16:07,821
Ju Ah was being really prickly.

234
00:16:08,121 --> 00:16:13,101
I can tell. She takes after you,
being all prickly like that.

235
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:17,371
- Go to bed.
- You too, and stop fussing.

236
00:16:18,031 --> 00:16:20,971
And all this...
I'll take care of it later.

237
00:16:21,371 --> 00:16:23,671
Seriously...
It's always "later" with you.

238
00:16:23,811 --> 00:16:26,171
How can you be exactly the same,
even when I'm sick?

239
00:16:27,011 --> 00:16:29,681
You wouldn't even care if I died,
would you?

240
00:16:29,981 --> 00:16:32,651
What? You told me
not to treat you like a patient.

241
00:16:32,751 --> 00:16:35,251
It's only stage two,
so you're not even a real patient.

242
00:16:35,251 --> 00:16:38,151
You're Han Seong Mi, one and only.

243
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:40,021
Don't act all weak. Got it?

244
00:16:40,161 --> 00:16:43,061
Yes, you're right.
Hearing you say that really...

245
00:16:43,131 --> 00:16:45,161
makes me feel so much stronger.

246
00:16:45,861 --> 00:16:47,431
Good grief.

247
00:16:49,161 --> 00:16:51,171
Unbelievable.

248
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:55,841
I don't know
why I even bother talking.

249
00:16:58,011 --> 00:17:02,011
- It's a revitalizing health plan.
- Ma'am.

250
00:17:02,481 --> 00:17:05,511
Did you watch the show?
Thank you so much.

251
00:17:05,611 --> 00:17:08,381
And by the way,
I'm opening a new store.

252
00:17:08,451 --> 00:17:11,621
You should come by sometime.
Yes, of course. I'll be in touch.

253
00:17:12,691 --> 00:17:15,761
Honey, that's enough. Okay?
It's getting really late.

254
00:17:16,261 --> 00:17:18,391
You're right.
Look at me getting carried away.

255
00:17:18,461 --> 00:17:20,331
I'll make the rest of my calls
tomorrow.

256
00:17:20,531 --> 00:17:23,871
Come on, no need for any more calls.
Look at these views.

257
00:17:24,971 --> 00:17:28,341
My goodness, honey,
I think this is a huge hit.

258
00:17:28,501 --> 00:17:31,771
If we get this much recognition,
getting the council nomination...

259
00:17:31,841 --> 00:17:34,841
- should be a cakewalk.
- You think so?

260
00:17:36,381 --> 00:17:41,181
You were worried someone might
recognize you and leave a comment.

261
00:17:41,521 --> 00:17:42,521
Why?

262
00:17:42,851 --> 00:17:46,421
Did someone leave a comment?
Did they write my real name?

263
00:17:46,621 --> 00:17:49,291
I went through all of them,

264
00:17:50,091 --> 00:17:54,161
- and there's nothing. Don't worry.
- Really?

265
00:17:54,531 --> 00:17:55,931
Thank goodness.

266
00:17:57,171 --> 00:17:58,871
A star is born. Absolutely.

267
00:18:00,471 --> 00:18:01,471
A star is born.

268
00:18:08,611 --> 00:18:09,611
My gosh!

269
00:18:20,121 --> 00:18:21,461
What do you think you're doing?

270
00:18:22,191 --> 00:18:24,191
I told you not to act
like you know me!

271
00:18:26,161 --> 00:18:27,861
And why should I do that?

272
00:18:28,131 --> 00:18:29,971
You're going to act like this
after taking my money?

273
00:18:30,371 --> 00:18:32,471
Your husband is the director
of a traditional medicine clinic,

274
00:18:32,631 --> 00:18:35,441
and it looks like
you're opening a respectable store.

275
00:18:36,141 --> 00:18:38,711
You really think that paltry sum
is enough to buy my silence?

276
00:18:40,611 --> 00:18:41,941
You...

277
00:18:41,941 --> 00:18:45,151
You abandoned your child
to turn your life around,

278
00:18:45,381 --> 00:18:47,221
so you have to pay for it.

279
00:18:50,621 --> 00:18:52,051
"Abandoned?"

280
00:18:53,161 --> 00:18:56,061
I told you I got rid of the baby.
She's dead!

281
00:18:58,731 --> 00:19:00,031
Hey!

282
00:19:00,361 --> 00:19:02,301
How can you lie and say
your daughter is dead...

283
00:19:02,731 --> 00:19:05,071
when she's perfectly alive?

284
00:19:09,701 --> 00:19:13,381
Your precious family
that you care so much about...

285
00:19:13,841 --> 00:19:16,751
What do you think will happen
when they find out the truth?

286
00:19:18,281 --> 00:19:19,451
What?

287
00:19:50,251 --> 00:19:51,351
Mom.

288
00:19:54,381 --> 00:19:55,381
Eun Bin.

289
00:19:57,351 --> 00:19:58,621
Why are you down here?

290
00:20:00,621 --> 00:20:02,821
What's wrong?
Did you have another nightmare?

291
00:20:03,391 --> 00:20:06,561
Yes. A really awful nightmare.

292
00:20:08,601 --> 00:20:10,231
Come here. Let me give you a hug.

293
00:20:14,201 --> 00:20:17,141
Gosh, you were doing so well
for a while. What's bothering you?

294
00:20:18,241 --> 00:20:21,281
Was it about your birth mother
abandoning you?

295
00:20:23,181 --> 00:20:24,181
Yes.

296
00:20:26,051 --> 00:20:27,151
Don't you worry.

297
00:20:28,421 --> 00:20:29,721
I won't leave you.

298
00:20:31,551 --> 00:20:32,551
Never.

299
00:20:33,361 --> 00:20:35,191
I will never, ever leave my Eun Bin.

300
00:20:36,661 --> 00:20:37,691
You promise?

301
00:20:39,091 --> 00:20:40,101
Of course.

302
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:25,241
This is it.

303
00:21:26,611 --> 00:21:28,581
You went out in the dead of night
to buy avocados?

304
00:21:29,381 --> 00:21:33,651
It wasn't easy finding ones
that were perfectly ripe.

305
00:21:35,121 --> 00:21:37,551
- Keep your voice down.
- Okay.

306
00:21:38,021 --> 00:21:40,921
I read that they can help kill
breast cancer cells...

307
00:21:41,221 --> 00:21:43,731
and even boost anticancer activity.

308
00:21:43,731 --> 00:21:45,961
So I thought I'd make
a few different things for her.

309
00:21:47,201 --> 00:21:51,101
- Your wife is going to love this.
- Just tell her you did it.

310
00:21:51,671 --> 00:21:53,201
You did all the work.
Why should I take the credit?

311
00:21:53,541 --> 00:21:58,111
I don't want her to think
I'm doing it because she's sick.

312
00:21:58,241 --> 00:22:01,941
Plus, she might get mad and say
I'm treating her like a patient.

313
00:22:03,851 --> 00:22:06,951
Okay, say I made it before I left.
I have to head out early anyway.

314
00:22:07,321 --> 00:22:09,951
Why? Got a date this early?

315
00:22:11,191 --> 00:22:12,191
Something like that.

316
00:22:12,651 --> 00:22:16,661
If she's good, don't drag your feet.
You should get remarried. Okay?

317
00:22:16,861 --> 00:22:21,301
If you still want a kid so badly,
you need to hurry up, man.

318
00:22:23,201 --> 00:22:24,201
I know.

319
00:22:27,601 --> 00:22:31,211
Basketball this early?
You're going to wear Mr. Gong out.

320
00:22:31,771 --> 00:22:32,871
You think this was my idea?

321
00:22:35,181 --> 00:22:36,511
Should I come along too?

322
00:22:37,081 --> 00:22:40,651
Sure. I'll leave after one game,
then you two can go on your date.

323
00:22:41,781 --> 00:22:43,991
Okay. Then let's eat breakfast
and get ready.

324
00:22:49,661 --> 00:22:50,791
Just eat your food.

325
00:22:51,091 --> 00:22:53,331
Just a second, Dad.
I'm just checking the ratings.

326
00:22:54,561 --> 00:22:58,131
Yes! The ratings are great.
Honey, they're great!

327
00:22:58,831 --> 00:23:01,571
That's wonderful news.
Right, Hyun Bin?

328
00:23:01,841 --> 00:23:04,641
Yes, Dad. At this rate,
you're going to get really famous.

329
00:23:04,771 --> 00:23:08,741
Famous? I'm going way beyond famous.
I'm going to be a global superstar.

330
00:23:08,841 --> 00:23:11,851
Here we go. It's happening.
I feel the energy.

331
00:23:12,681 --> 00:23:14,881
My friends were all texting me
about how much they enjoyed it.

332
00:23:15,721 --> 00:23:18,121
Ji Hu, Min Seo has something to say.

333
00:23:21,721 --> 00:23:26,631
I'll head home after I help
Ji Hu through his midterm.

334
00:23:26,691 --> 00:23:29,461
Oh, my. Why? Did your parents
ask you to come home?

335
00:23:29,661 --> 00:23:31,731
No, it's not that.

336
00:23:31,971 --> 00:23:34,401
If that's not it,
you should stay a little longer.

337
00:23:34,801 --> 00:23:37,641
That's right. I'll double your pay.

338
00:23:38,041 --> 00:23:39,071
Do you really have to go?

339
00:23:39,511 --> 00:23:44,011
She's already made up her mind.
Why is everyone making this awkward?

340
00:23:44,111 --> 00:23:48,481
It's a shame. Ji Hu was starting
to get into his English lessons.

341
00:23:48,951 --> 00:23:52,291
I'll keep helping him until I leave
and check in from the US too.

342
00:23:52,721 --> 00:23:57,031
If Ji Hu decides to study abroad,
please be sure to contact me.

343
00:23:57,261 --> 00:23:59,991
My whole family would be thrilled
to welcome him.

344
00:24:00,061 --> 00:24:01,801
Studying abroad is
out of the question.

345
00:24:03,431 --> 00:24:05,371
Our stepmom seems to be
taking it the hardest.

346
00:24:06,071 --> 00:24:07,901
Oh, I suppose I am.

347
00:24:08,201 --> 00:24:11,411
She's helped us out so much,
and I've gotten really attached.

348
00:24:11,871 --> 00:24:15,411
There's still time.
And since you start work tomorrow,

349
00:24:15,511 --> 00:24:19,311
- I can help you out until I leave.
- Okay, thank you.

350
00:24:19,611 --> 00:24:20,621
Of course.

351
00:24:25,291 --> 00:24:27,821
What is it?
Just get to the point and say it.

352
00:24:29,091 --> 00:24:30,091
Well...

353
00:24:30,931 --> 00:24:33,601
As Se Ri embarks on a new chapter,

354
00:24:34,161 --> 00:24:36,331
I'd like to give her a gift.

355
00:24:36,731 --> 00:24:38,401
Then do it. Why are you asking me?

356
00:24:39,471 --> 00:24:41,001
Because I need
your permission for this.

357
00:24:43,741 --> 00:24:44,971
What if Hyun Bin and Eun Bin...

358
00:24:45,811 --> 00:24:48,541
were officially adopted by Se Ri?

359
00:24:50,681 --> 00:24:52,381
- Adopted?
- Yes.

360
00:24:52,981 --> 00:24:55,181
Right now, Se Ri is only
legally my spouse.

361
00:24:55,651 --> 00:24:58,291
They call her Mom,
and she's their stepmother in name,

362
00:24:58,991 --> 00:25:00,291
but there's no legal tie
between them.

363
00:25:05,261 --> 00:25:06,261
Do it.

364
00:25:07,131 --> 00:25:08,261
Does that mean you approve, Dad?

365
00:25:09,201 --> 00:25:10,701
You should have done it sooner.

366
00:25:14,901 --> 00:25:16,241
Are you serious, Dad?

367
00:25:16,641 --> 00:25:19,511
Of course, I am.
I should have done this ages ago.

368
00:25:20,511 --> 00:25:21,781
It feels a bit overdue.

369
00:25:22,511 --> 00:25:24,181
Why? You don't like it?

370
00:25:24,381 --> 00:25:28,621
No, it's not that. I'm just grateful
that you've made this decision, Dad.

371
00:25:29,551 --> 00:25:31,921
Look, I have my own trauma
from it all.

372
00:25:32,421 --> 00:25:33,661
And I'm sure you kids do too.

373
00:25:34,291 --> 00:25:36,991
What if she decided to leave us,
just like your mother did?

374
00:25:37,191 --> 00:25:39,861
And I was afraid of legal trouble
if that happened.

375
00:25:40,231 --> 00:25:42,331
So you trust her completely now,
right?

376
00:25:43,161 --> 00:25:44,171
Of course, I do.

377
00:25:45,571 --> 00:25:46,571
Eun Bin, what about you?

378
00:25:47,401 --> 00:25:50,071
What's the difference
if we're legally family?

379
00:25:50,711 --> 00:25:53,641
It means you'll officially be listed
as Se Ri's children.

380
00:25:53,941 --> 00:25:57,511
- So we'll inherit her assets?
- Yang Eun Bin!

381
00:25:58,051 --> 00:26:02,081
What? Many things in this house are
in her name, and so is the new shop.

382
00:26:02,581 --> 00:26:04,651
Wow, you can be so calculating
sometimes.

383
00:26:04,751 --> 00:26:07,591
You brat. So, are you in or not?

384
00:26:07,691 --> 00:26:10,331
I'm in. Let's do it quickly,
before Mom can run off.

385
00:26:10,931 --> 00:26:14,701
Stepmother... I mean, Mother
is going to be so thrilled.

386
00:26:21,301 --> 00:26:22,341
What?

387
00:26:23,241 --> 00:26:25,071
Is this really happening?

388
00:26:28,111 --> 00:26:29,511
You must be so happy.

389
00:26:31,411 --> 00:26:32,411
Yes.

390
00:26:33,051 --> 00:26:36,351
You've been crying a lot lately,
Mother.

391
00:26:38,821 --> 00:26:41,121
"Mother?"

392
00:26:41,921 --> 00:26:44,061
Yes. I'll call you Mother
from now on.

393
00:26:45,631 --> 00:26:46,631
Eun Bin.

394
00:26:47,661 --> 00:26:49,361
Did you really agree to this too?

395
00:26:49,661 --> 00:26:53,031
Yes. I was already calling you Mom,
so...

396
00:26:53,431 --> 00:26:54,901
I've already given my blessing
as well.

397
00:26:56,201 --> 00:26:57,271
Father.

398
00:27:00,381 --> 00:27:01,381
Thank you, Eun Bin.

399
00:27:02,941 --> 00:27:04,081
Thank you, Hyun Bin.

400
00:27:06,381 --> 00:27:09,421
Honey, I promise
I'll do my very best.

401
00:27:11,021 --> 00:27:12,521
I should have done this sooner.

402
00:27:13,151 --> 00:27:14,721
I'm sorry it took so long, Se Ri.

403
00:27:31,941 --> 00:27:33,841
I wonder if I packed too much
for the three of us.

404
00:27:34,411 --> 00:27:36,041
It's fine. I'll eat a lot.

405
00:27:37,981 --> 00:27:40,621
Auntie Se Ri must be so happy,
don't you think?

406
00:27:41,081 --> 00:27:42,121
I bet.

407
00:27:42,181 --> 00:27:45,591
She always seemed to feel left out,
like she wasn't part of the family.

408
00:27:46,621 --> 00:27:49,361
Mom, don't mention this to Mr. Gong.

409
00:27:49,761 --> 00:27:51,091
He might feel pressured.

410
00:27:51,461 --> 00:27:52,461
What?

411
00:27:52,731 --> 00:27:54,201
It'll be hard enough for you two...

412
00:27:54,201 --> 00:27:56,131
to get your feuding families'
approval.

413
00:27:56,761 --> 00:28:00,271
And honestly, I feel awkward
being stuck in the middle of it all.

414
00:28:04,471 --> 00:28:05,971
Why would you think that?

415
00:28:06,241 --> 00:28:08,781
Even as we're on our way
to play basketball with him...

416
00:28:09,481 --> 00:28:10,581
You know what?

417
00:28:11,011 --> 00:28:13,251
I think I understand
why Hyun Bin went to study abroad.

418
00:28:14,781 --> 00:28:17,951
I just want you and Mr. Gong
to be happy together.

419
00:28:19,521 --> 00:28:20,761
Are you really going
to be like this?

420
00:28:22,021 --> 00:28:24,131
Why did Min Seo have to bring up
studying abroad?

421
00:28:26,431 --> 00:28:28,431
You listen to me very carefully.

422
00:28:28,831 --> 00:28:31,431
We're a package deal. Got it?

423
00:28:31,571 --> 00:28:34,171
Mom, that's such a selfish way
to think.

424
00:28:35,441 --> 00:28:37,171
Mr. Gong wanted to have kids,
didn't he?

425
00:28:37,471 --> 00:28:39,071
And you even teased him about it.

426
00:28:39,171 --> 00:28:42,981
So what? You want me to have a baby?
Don't be ridiculous.

427
00:28:48,421 --> 00:28:49,421
Yes, Mr. Gong.

428
00:28:50,851 --> 00:28:52,091
Okay.

429
00:28:52,721 --> 00:28:53,721
What is it?

430
00:28:54,591 --> 00:28:55,661
It's okay.

431
00:28:56,221 --> 00:28:57,431
Yes, I understand.

432
00:29:00,031 --> 00:29:01,301
He said he can't make it today.

433
00:29:01,631 --> 00:29:02,631
What?

434
00:29:02,731 --> 00:29:05,371
That's okay. I had some studying
to do before my extra class anyway.

435
00:29:08,541 --> 00:29:10,871
I'm going to a study cafe,
so you can head on in.

436
00:29:10,941 --> 00:29:13,171
- Okay?
- Yes, okay.

437
00:29:19,381 --> 00:29:21,651
(Vitamin)

438
00:29:29,121 --> 00:29:30,361
What are you up to?

439
00:29:31,961 --> 00:29:34,431
I'm preparing some study materials
for Ji Hu.

440
00:29:35,831 --> 00:29:38,031
Did you let them know
you're coming home?

441
00:29:39,271 --> 00:29:41,401
- Not yet.
- Why not?

442
00:29:42,071 --> 00:29:46,941
Do you think I should bug the Sister
for my birth mom's contact info?

443
00:29:47,311 --> 00:29:49,911
Or should I just ask her
to at least tell me where she lives?

444
00:29:50,681 --> 00:29:52,781
But you said your birth mom
doesn't want to see you.

445
00:29:53,251 --> 00:29:54,251
Exactly.

446
00:29:55,521 --> 00:29:57,851
I just want to confront her
and ask her why.

447
00:29:58,321 --> 00:30:01,461
Should I get revenge
like they do in the movies?

448
00:30:01,961 --> 00:30:05,361
Should I be a villain, ruin her joy,
and take everything she has?

449
00:30:05,891 --> 00:30:07,231
Are you serious?

450
00:30:08,501 --> 00:30:09,761
I'm kidding.

451
00:30:12,371 --> 00:30:15,971
But if you did find out
where she lives,

452
00:30:16,041 --> 00:30:17,411
what would you want to do?

453
00:30:18,941 --> 00:30:21,411
Since she said
she doesn't want to see me,

454
00:30:22,511 --> 00:30:24,551
I'd just want to see her from afar.

455
00:30:25,581 --> 00:30:27,251
If I ever get the chance,

456
00:30:27,721 --> 00:30:29,951
I'd love to hold her hand,
just once.

457
00:30:30,791 --> 00:30:32,551
And help her
if she's going through a hard time.

458
00:30:33,791 --> 00:30:35,561
I'm sure she's doing fine.

459
00:30:35,561 --> 00:30:38,361
You showing up now
will make things harder for her.

460
00:30:39,091 --> 00:30:41,431
Yes, I guess you're right.

461
00:30:42,961 --> 00:30:46,631
By staying away,
I guess I'm helping her.

462
00:30:57,711 --> 00:30:58,711
Wait a minute.

463
00:30:59,511 --> 00:31:02,551
It's Sunday.
Why do you need to go out again?

464
00:31:02,851 --> 00:31:05,791
They're finalizing the hair
and makeup for the show.

465
00:31:06,191 --> 00:31:08,591
Are you sure you're okay
with doing the fashion show?

466
00:31:09,321 --> 00:31:14,101
Ju Ah seems determined to do well.
She's so on edge about it.

467
00:31:15,201 --> 00:31:18,401
It looks like she and Jun Hyeok
broke up after all.

468
00:31:20,671 --> 00:31:21,941
You're not surprised?

469
00:31:22,471 --> 00:31:26,671
No, not really.
That happens when you're young.

470
00:31:27,481 --> 00:31:31,681
Mother, I'll drive today,
so please don't make Ju Ah do it.

471
00:31:31,751 --> 00:31:34,621
She looked like she didn't
get any sleep at breakfast.

472
00:31:35,021 --> 00:31:38,721
Jeong Han can drive on his day off.
Should I say something?

473
00:31:40,721 --> 00:31:42,461
- Yes, sure. Of course.
- Hey, listen...

474
00:31:42,621 --> 00:31:44,661
Anything's fine with me. Yes.

475
00:31:46,031 --> 00:31:47,761
Okay, sure. Where to?

476
00:31:49,301 --> 00:31:51,131
Oh, for goodness' sake.

477
00:31:52,401 --> 00:31:55,871
My brother-in-law makes me breakfast
to make sure I'm eating healthy,

478
00:31:56,341 --> 00:31:58,111
and then there's my husband.
I just don't get it.

479
00:31:58,471 --> 00:32:00,781
Want me to give him
a piece of my mind?

480
00:32:00,911 --> 00:32:04,281
No, that's okay.
I don't want him to feel obligated.

481
00:32:04,811 --> 00:32:07,681
- Mom, you got everything?
- Yes. You pulled an all-nighter?

482
00:32:07,751 --> 00:32:08,781
I'll drive today.

483
00:32:08,851 --> 00:32:11,721
No, it's okay, I'll do it.
Grandma will kill me if I don't.

484
00:32:12,751 --> 00:32:13,791
Come on, let's go.

485
00:32:21,231 --> 00:32:22,501
Drive safe.

486
00:32:23,001 --> 00:32:25,071
If you get sleepy,
be sure to pull over and rest.

487
00:32:25,171 --> 00:32:26,901
I will, Grandma. Don't worry.

488
00:32:27,741 --> 00:32:29,771
Babe... I mean, Director.

489
00:32:30,711 --> 00:32:31,711
Good morning.

490
00:32:32,311 --> 00:32:34,011
My gosh, what brings you here again?

491
00:32:34,211 --> 00:32:37,611
You have your meeting today.
I came to give you a ride.

492
00:32:37,911 --> 00:32:41,221
That won't be necessary.
Ju Ah offered to drive today.

493
00:32:43,421 --> 00:32:47,591
By the look on Ms. Gong's face,
I doubt we can trust her driving.

494
00:32:53,731 --> 00:32:54,731
Come on.

495
00:32:55,261 --> 00:32:57,001
Shall we, Doctor?

496
00:32:57,331 --> 00:33:00,901
Also, I left my car yesterday
since I came in yours, remember?

497
00:33:04,411 --> 00:33:08,411
- Are you going to keep this up?
- Yes, I am.

498
00:33:08,911 --> 00:33:11,211
If you keep saying no,
I'll just have to tell Ms. Gong...

499
00:33:11,751 --> 00:33:13,651
No, fine. I get it.

500
00:33:17,951 --> 00:33:18,951
Please get in.

501
00:33:23,861 --> 00:33:24,861
All right.

502
00:33:25,091 --> 00:33:26,131
Closing the door.

503
00:33:29,661 --> 00:33:32,801
I'm not doing this to score points.
I'm just looking out for her.

504
00:33:33,501 --> 00:33:35,171
I didn't say a word.

505
00:33:36,341 --> 00:33:37,671
We'll be on our way, then.

506
00:33:38,511 --> 00:33:40,141
We're off, Grandma.

507
00:33:42,311 --> 00:33:45,251
Why didn't you tell me?
Do you always go behind my back?

508
00:33:46,351 --> 00:33:47,781
It's called a surprise.

509
00:33:59,461 --> 00:34:01,731
I was thinking of going with this
for the hair.

510
00:34:02,031 --> 00:34:03,301
What do you think, Dr. Han?

511
00:34:04,401 --> 00:34:08,401
It's lovely, but let's make sure
the clothes are the focus, not me.

512
00:34:08,471 --> 00:34:09,471
Of course.

513
00:34:09,941 --> 00:34:11,571
- For the makeup...
- Right.

514
00:34:11,571 --> 00:34:16,241
Your skin tone is so clear,
so let's keep the base very sheer.

515
00:34:16,811 --> 00:34:18,811
Yes, I like how natural it looks.

516
00:34:19,251 --> 00:34:23,181
Then, let's do a natural rose pink
for the lips...

517
00:34:23,251 --> 00:34:25,251
Something seems fishy.

518
00:34:26,091 --> 00:34:27,391
What? What's fishy?

519
00:34:27,561 --> 00:34:30,261
My mom, I mean. She kept saying no,

520
00:34:30,261 --> 00:34:33,931
so why is she suddenly letting you
do all this for her?

521
00:34:35,501 --> 00:34:39,731
Maybe she thinks it's a work perk,
not a favor from me.

522
00:34:41,101 --> 00:34:42,501
You don't think...

523
00:34:43,741 --> 00:34:45,341
I don't think, what?

524
00:34:48,341 --> 00:34:49,881
You don't think
she's starting to like you?

525
00:34:51,551 --> 00:34:54,321
If my mom's on our side,
it's a done deal.

526
00:34:54,381 --> 00:34:55,381
Right?

527
00:34:55,721 --> 00:34:56,721
Right.

528
00:34:57,081 --> 00:35:00,191
I'll try harder.
I'll even drive her home after this.

529
00:35:01,361 --> 00:35:04,661
Want to take the bus
to work with me tomorrow?

530
00:35:05,531 --> 00:35:07,961
Actually,
I'm taking the morning off tomorrow.

531
00:35:08,031 --> 00:35:09,801
I have to run an errand
at a government office.

532
00:35:10,131 --> 00:35:11,671
A government office? Why?

533
00:35:12,371 --> 00:35:16,471
We're starting the legal process
for our stepmom to adopt us.

534
00:35:17,101 --> 00:35:19,111
- Adoption?
- Yes.

535
00:35:19,671 --> 00:35:22,611
Until now,
she was legally just my dad's wife.

536
00:35:24,251 --> 00:35:25,781
I see.

537
00:35:26,511 --> 00:35:29,421
Now, we'll be
a legally recognized family.

538
00:35:30,891 --> 00:35:31,921
She must be so happy.

539
00:35:32,151 --> 00:35:35,891
Yes. I think she feels like
we're finally a real family.

540
00:35:50,141 --> 00:35:51,411
This is really good.

541
00:35:52,311 --> 00:35:54,111
Your phrasing is great,
and the flow is so natural.

542
00:35:54,641 --> 00:35:58,881
- Really?
- Yes. You're improving so quickly.

543
00:35:58,951 --> 00:36:01,351
I think you'd do great
even if you studied on your own.

544
00:36:02,151 --> 00:36:06,621
But I'm a little sad.
I enjoyed our sessions, Min Seo.

545
00:36:06,821 --> 00:36:11,091
Sorry for backing out, especially
since I was the one who offered.

546
00:36:11,831 --> 00:36:14,731
You don't have to be sorry,
but I am a little curious.

547
00:36:14,801 --> 00:36:16,401
About why you're leaving
so suddenly.

548
00:36:16,861 --> 00:36:21,571
The reason I came to Korea
is gone now.

549
00:36:22,071 --> 00:36:24,711
It turns out I can't meet the person
I came here to see.

550
00:36:24,841 --> 00:36:28,141
Who is it? I asked you before,
but you wouldn't tell me.

551
00:36:29,111 --> 00:36:30,411
- The truth is...
- Hey, Mom.

552
00:36:30,681 --> 00:36:33,151
After Min Seo leaves,
I can teach you English.

553
00:36:33,151 --> 00:36:35,551
I can teach you the basics,
at least.

554
00:36:36,121 --> 00:36:37,621
That's sweet of you, honey.

555
00:36:37,751 --> 00:36:39,251
I'm not just saying this.

556
00:36:39,251 --> 00:36:42,461
I'm going to start making breakfast
and doing chores around the house.

557
00:36:42,661 --> 00:36:44,831
Then should I go
help out at the shop?

558
00:36:44,891 --> 00:36:48,401
- No. I'm going to work at the shop.
- Really?

559
00:36:48,401 --> 00:36:50,831
Then can I help with the housework?

560
00:36:51,131 --> 00:36:53,271
Sure. But I'll handle breakfast.

561
00:36:54,441 --> 00:36:58,111
My gosh, look at my daughters
fighting over who gets to help.

562
00:36:58,971 --> 00:37:01,111
My gosh.
I don't know what's gotten into you.

563
00:37:03,411 --> 00:37:04,411
All right, then.

564
00:37:09,621 --> 00:37:11,391
If I end up studying abroad,

565
00:37:11,951 --> 00:37:13,251
we'd have to break up, wouldn't we?

566
00:37:14,091 --> 00:37:16,221
Where is this studying abroad talk
coming from all of a sudden?

567
00:37:16,791 --> 00:37:19,561
I was just thinking about it.

568
00:37:20,861 --> 00:37:23,231
Go study abroad. But...

569
00:37:23,861 --> 00:37:24,901
you have to take me with you.

570
00:37:26,001 --> 00:37:27,101
Should we do that?

571
00:37:27,771 --> 00:37:28,771
Go where, exactly?

572
00:37:29,341 --> 00:37:30,401
Who gave you permission?

573
00:37:33,241 --> 00:37:34,511
Hello.

574
00:37:36,481 --> 00:37:37,481
We keep running into each other.

575
00:37:38,281 --> 00:37:40,381
Sorry to interrupt your date.

576
00:37:40,951 --> 00:37:42,581
I just had something to give Ji Hu.

577
00:37:49,661 --> 00:37:50,661
Here you go.

578
00:37:59,671 --> 00:38:00,731
How did you get this?

579
00:38:00,971 --> 00:38:04,741
I heard this is all the rage
with middle schoolers, right?

580
00:38:05,841 --> 00:38:06,911
My gosh.

581
00:38:08,581 --> 00:38:09,581
You like it?

582
00:38:10,841 --> 00:38:15,351
Like it? He loves it!
Ji Hu has been dying to get this.

583
00:38:15,751 --> 00:38:17,081
I'm glad to hear that.

584
00:38:18,421 --> 00:38:20,221
Sorry, I missed our basketball game
this morning.

585
00:38:20,991 --> 00:38:24,331
Hey, that was the first time I ever
lined up before a store opened.

586
00:38:24,391 --> 00:38:26,391
You wouldn't believe
how long the line was.

587
00:38:29,001 --> 00:38:31,401
To make up for it, how about a game
of basketball later?

588
00:38:33,031 --> 00:38:35,301
Hey, what are you laughing at?
Back in my day,

589
00:38:35,371 --> 00:38:37,001
I had some serious
dribbling skills...

590
00:38:39,641 --> 00:38:41,781
Let's play ball, then have your mom
join us for dinner.

591
00:38:43,511 --> 00:38:46,411
Go ahead.
I have math tutoring anyway.

592
00:38:47,381 --> 00:38:49,551
And just so you know,
Ji Hu isn't going to study abroad.

593
00:38:49,881 --> 00:38:53,251
- Got it?
- Yes. I wasn't a fan of it anyway.

594
00:38:54,251 --> 00:38:57,261
This is really calling my name.
Mind if I have some?

595
00:38:57,761 --> 00:38:59,631
My legs are killing me
from waiting all day.

596
00:39:01,101 --> 00:39:03,861
Oh, not bad. All right, come on.

597
00:39:07,571 --> 00:39:08,571
Man...

598
00:39:15,411 --> 00:39:17,281
Nice! Hey, come on!

599
00:39:18,351 --> 00:39:21,121
Oh, Dong Suk!

600
00:39:22,121 --> 00:39:24,051
- Dong Suk!
- Mom, give us a minute.

601
00:39:24,151 --> 00:39:27,151
Just a moment. Hey. Dong Suk!

602
00:39:27,761 --> 00:39:29,821
Hold on. Come on!

603
00:39:32,691 --> 00:39:33,691
Here.

604
00:39:37,831 --> 00:39:38,931
Ji Hu.

605
00:39:39,231 --> 00:39:40,571
Why did you bring up
studying abroad earlier?

606
00:39:41,701 --> 00:39:43,241
Don't tell me it was because
of me and your mom, was it?

607
00:39:44,001 --> 00:39:46,771
Yes. Am I in the way of you two?

608
00:39:49,011 --> 00:39:50,311
You want me to let you in
on a little secret?

609
00:39:52,151 --> 00:39:53,381
Having you in her life...

610
00:39:54,751 --> 00:39:55,781
makes me love your mom
that much more.

611
00:39:58,421 --> 00:39:59,421
There.

612
00:40:05,161 --> 00:40:08,401
I tried to get him one a few times,
but they were so hard to find.

613
00:40:09,901 --> 00:40:12,071
I'm telling you, I was so nervous...

614
00:40:12,871 --> 00:40:14,401
that they were going to sell out.

615
00:40:16,071 --> 00:40:17,101
Thank you.

616
00:40:18,311 --> 00:40:22,141
You're busy with your sister-in-law.
You didn't have to do this.

617
00:40:22,641 --> 00:40:24,651
I'm Superman.

618
00:40:25,781 --> 00:40:27,111
I told you. I can handle both.

619
00:40:29,781 --> 00:40:30,781
Listen...

620
00:40:34,521 --> 00:40:35,521
I...

621
00:40:36,321 --> 00:40:37,891
I don't want to have another child.

622
00:40:38,731 --> 00:40:42,161
I just felt like I had to tell you.

623
00:40:43,401 --> 00:40:46,171
I know you wanted to have a child.

624
00:40:47,771 --> 00:40:49,071
What? Why would we need another kid?

625
00:40:50,401 --> 00:40:51,471
We've got one right over there.

626
00:40:53,511 --> 00:40:55,711
Come on, you know how hard it is
to raise a child.

627
00:40:56,711 --> 00:40:59,251
Gosh, just playing basketball
with him...

628
00:40:59,811 --> 00:41:01,381
I already feel like
I'm about to collapse.

629
00:41:02,551 --> 00:41:05,251
Hey, wait a minute.
If we had a kid now,

630
00:41:06,021 --> 00:41:08,061
would I have to play basketball
until I'm 60? Good grief.

631
00:41:08,661 --> 00:41:10,261
No way. I'm not doing it. No.

632
00:41:10,961 --> 00:41:12,191
Oh, boy. I can't do it.

633
00:41:13,761 --> 00:41:14,761
Dong Suk.

634
00:41:16,131 --> 00:41:18,031
Do you know what Ji Hu means to me?

635
00:41:19,971 --> 00:41:22,541
The one thing I've always wanted,
something so precious.

636
00:41:22,971 --> 00:41:26,111
After a long wait,
I'm just about to get it,

637
00:41:26,211 --> 00:41:28,681
and then a sales clerk calls me.
"Excuse me, sir."

638
00:41:29,311 --> 00:41:30,311
That item...

639
00:41:31,311 --> 00:41:32,581
It's buy one, get one free.

640
00:41:34,921 --> 00:41:37,781
It's so amazing, it blows your mind.
That's exactly how I feel.

641
00:41:42,891 --> 00:41:44,191
Don't send Ji Hu to study abroad.

642
00:41:45,531 --> 00:41:46,631
That's not who you are.

643
00:41:47,731 --> 00:41:48,901
If you were that kind of person,

644
00:41:50,601 --> 00:41:51,601
I couldn't love you.

645
00:41:55,141 --> 00:41:56,141
Ji Hu!

646
00:41:56,941 --> 00:41:58,541
Pass! Here!

647
00:41:59,171 --> 00:42:00,171
Come on!

648
00:42:02,341 --> 00:42:03,511
Come on, hey!

649
00:42:04,711 --> 00:42:05,711
Hey!

650
00:42:20,831 --> 00:42:24,101
Could you dim the lights a bit?
I'm afraid we'll lose the details.

651
00:42:26,331 --> 00:42:29,141
She pulled an all-nighter yesterday,
but you'd never know by her energy.

652
00:42:30,501 --> 00:42:32,211
That's because her sense
of responsibility is off the charts.

653
00:42:33,041 --> 00:42:35,641
Plus, you're the main model
for this, Doctor.

654
00:42:36,581 --> 00:42:38,351
For her, this is practically
a dream come true.

655
00:42:38,611 --> 00:42:40,081
You can imagine
how nervous she must be.

656
00:42:40,851 --> 00:42:43,921
She personally selected every look
for the entire collection,

657
00:42:44,321 --> 00:42:45,851
refined all the styling,

658
00:42:46,191 --> 00:42:48,121
and is directing everything,
including...

659
00:42:48,321 --> 00:42:51,121
the music and the lighting.
The whole show, really.

660
00:42:55,501 --> 00:42:56,601
Oh, I mean...

661
00:42:57,001 --> 00:43:00,801
The company has very high
expectations for Ms. Gong.

662
00:43:29,461 --> 00:43:31,701
Director Yang, do you still
have feelings for my Ju Ah?

663
00:43:34,531 --> 00:43:38,471
Unless I'm mistaken,
that's certainly how it looks to me.

664
00:43:39,771 --> 00:43:43,881
It's not just that I'm your model,
or because of my situation.

665
00:43:44,511 --> 00:43:49,021
I wonder if you're trying to get on
my or Ju Ah's good side.

666
00:43:51,121 --> 00:43:52,221
That's...

667
00:43:52,821 --> 00:43:57,091
Since she and Jun Hyeok broke up,
if you plan on dating Ju Ah...

668
00:43:58,691 --> 00:44:01,601
Forget it.
It's never going to happen.

669
00:44:05,071 --> 00:44:06,371
I know I'm crossing a line.

670
00:44:07,171 --> 00:44:08,171
If I'm wrong,

671
00:44:08,501 --> 00:44:10,071
then I'm sorry,
but please try to understand.

672
00:44:10,641 --> 00:44:13,171
Like it or not, I'm Ju Ah's mother,

673
00:44:13,971 --> 00:44:17,781
and it's my job
to help her find happiness.

674
00:44:20,411 --> 00:44:21,981
Head toward your place,
Director Yang.

675
00:44:22,251 --> 00:44:23,281
We can switch drivers there.

676
00:44:24,951 --> 00:44:27,251
I'll see you to your door
and walk back from there.

677
00:44:27,351 --> 00:44:30,261
Just do as I say.
It's easier for me that way.

678
00:44:44,401 --> 00:44:45,941
Don't do this again.

679
00:44:46,611 --> 00:44:48,911
- No, I'll just...
- My gosh.

680
00:44:50,211 --> 00:44:52,381
Son!
Why were you in the driver's seat?

681
00:45:04,361 --> 00:45:05,391
Hello.

682
00:45:06,731 --> 00:45:09,161
I just don't understand this.

683
00:45:10,331 --> 00:45:11,331
Son.

684
00:45:11,831 --> 00:45:14,841
Were you just playing chauffeur?

685
00:45:15,441 --> 00:45:19,111
Chauffeur? Of course not.
Dr. Han is our model, so...

686
00:45:19,171 --> 00:45:22,981
Exactly!
Your company hired her as a model.

687
00:45:23,281 --> 00:45:26,511
So why is a director doing this
when you have other staff?

688
00:45:28,651 --> 00:45:29,781
She's your own mother.

689
00:45:30,151 --> 00:45:33,551
And to top it off, he's your boss,
and you were sleeping in the back?

690
00:45:34,421 --> 00:45:35,921
- I'm sorry.
- No, it's just...

691
00:45:35,991 --> 00:45:37,921
- Excuse me!
- Let's go inside and talk.

692
00:45:38,021 --> 00:45:39,331
Doctor, please, go on in.

693
00:45:39,461 --> 00:45:42,001
Let go! Why make someone else's
precious son your chauffeur?

694
00:45:42,061 --> 00:45:43,831
- Does she think she's a queen?
- They can hear you.

695
00:45:43,901 --> 00:45:46,431
- I want them to hear me!
- Mother, please, that's enough!

696
00:45:46,501 --> 00:45:49,571
Why were you the one driving?

697
00:45:49,701 --> 00:45:50,871
Is she your mother-in-law
or something?

698
00:45:51,301 --> 00:45:53,741
I don't even ask you to drive me.
You know why?

699
00:45:53,811 --> 00:45:55,741
Because you're my precious,
darling son.

700
00:45:56,681 --> 00:45:58,781
- This is so irritating.
- Wait...

701
00:46:08,021 --> 00:46:09,421
Unbelievable!

702
00:46:09,791 --> 00:46:12,331
He gives me a ride one time,
and I have to hear all that.

703
00:46:12,531 --> 00:46:15,301
Why did you tell him
to come here first?

704
00:46:15,301 --> 00:46:16,961
You could've had him
drop us off at home.

705
00:46:17,601 --> 00:46:19,971
Fine, it's my fault
for not steering clear of that mess.

706
00:46:20,401 --> 00:46:23,171
Mom, why would you say that?
Honestly.

707
00:46:24,271 --> 00:46:27,411
You'd think he was her son.
Like she gave birth to him.

708
00:46:27,841 --> 00:46:29,311
She's planning to legally adopt him
as an adult.

709
00:46:29,841 --> 00:46:31,411
So he might as well be.

710
00:46:32,311 --> 00:46:33,311
What?

711
00:46:35,421 --> 00:46:38,151
Don't hang around Director Yang.
You understand?

712
00:46:38,291 --> 00:46:40,821
Get on her bad side,
and you'll be her next target.

713
00:46:40,991 --> 00:46:45,361
- Mom, that's a bit much.
- Hey, did you forget what she did?

714
00:46:48,731 --> 00:46:49,731
Anyway,

715
00:46:50,361 --> 00:46:52,931
Director Yang's chances of marriage
are shot.

716
00:46:53,871 --> 00:46:54,901
My gosh!

717
00:46:59,511 --> 00:47:02,411
Goodness, we never
should have accepted his help.

718
00:47:02,741 --> 00:47:05,411
It wasn't like that.
He was just looking out for...

719
00:47:06,511 --> 00:47:07,511
Just go on up.

720
00:47:08,421 --> 00:47:11,421
I swear, if it wasn't for you,
I would've quit modeling already.

721
00:47:11,951 --> 00:47:14,921
- Please, stop. I get it, okay?
- Oh, honestly.

722
00:47:15,361 --> 00:47:16,921
Gong Ju Ah, go on up, now.

723
00:47:22,031 --> 00:47:24,261
And you, calm down.

724
00:47:24,761 --> 00:47:26,331
This isn't good for you.

725
00:47:27,731 --> 00:47:28,741
I'm sorry.

726
00:47:30,441 --> 00:47:31,971
Gosh, seriously...

727
00:47:58,031 --> 00:47:59,031
Oh, gosh. Hey.

728
00:48:00,331 --> 00:48:02,601
Where have you been all day?

729
00:48:03,471 --> 00:48:04,601
Well...

730
00:48:04,971 --> 00:48:07,071
I was busy preparing a proposal
for a speaking engagement.

731
00:48:07,841 --> 00:48:09,081
A speaking engagement?
All of a sudden?

732
00:48:09,541 --> 00:48:12,111
Now that I have TV experience
thanks to "Human Theater,"

733
00:48:12,351 --> 00:48:15,021
I thought I'd take this opportunity
to do lectures and public speaking.

734
00:48:15,581 --> 00:48:17,951
What, trying to become
a celebrity doctor or something?

735
00:48:18,181 --> 00:48:21,251
What? Scared I'll become
a bigger star than you?

736
00:48:21,721 --> 00:48:26,461
- A rising star.
- I can't with you and your words.

737
00:48:32,431 --> 00:48:33,531
Director Song.

738
00:48:34,171 --> 00:48:35,301
Hey, Seong Mi. How are you feeling?

739
00:48:35,901 --> 00:48:37,871
Come on. I'm perfectly fine.

740
00:48:38,571 --> 00:48:39,571
But why are you calling?

741
00:48:40,271 --> 00:48:42,041
Right. You're going to be fine.

742
00:48:43,081 --> 00:48:45,211
Seong Mi, I'm at my wits' end.

743
00:48:45,551 --> 00:48:46,781
You have to talk some sense
into Jeong Han.

744
00:48:47,651 --> 00:48:51,521
What are you talking about?
Did Ju Ah's dad go to see you today?

745
00:48:52,891 --> 00:48:55,561
Don't tell me he asked you
to put him on a show.

746
00:48:56,161 --> 00:49:01,091
Yes, I recommended some good shows,
but it all fell through.

747
00:49:01,601 --> 00:49:04,061
But now Jeong Han is saying
he'll do all the legwork,

748
00:49:04,561 --> 00:49:06,331
and he's making a scene,
begging for even a tiny segment.

749
00:49:06,901 --> 00:49:11,401
How humiliating.
Why on earth would he do that?

750
00:49:12,041 --> 00:49:13,941
He feels guilty
for putting you through so much.

751
00:49:14,611 --> 00:49:15,781
He says he'll do anything
to make it right.

752
00:49:38,771 --> 00:49:40,371
(Benefits of avocado)

753
00:49:43,441 --> 00:49:45,511
(Avocado bibimbap)

754
00:49:49,881 --> 00:49:54,081
- Hey.
- You're the one who made breakfast?

755
00:49:56,081 --> 00:49:58,721
Hey. You...
Why are you looking at that?

756
00:49:58,791 --> 00:49:59,791
My goodness.

757
00:50:00,291 --> 00:50:02,391
If you were worried,
you could've just said so.

758
00:50:02,721 --> 00:50:04,361
Why do you have to do things
behind my back?

759
00:50:06,431 --> 00:50:09,701
You feel one way but say another.
Could you be a little nicer?

760
00:50:15,371 --> 00:50:17,241
If I act worried,

761
00:50:18,201 --> 00:50:20,041
I was afraid it would make it
harder on you.

762
00:50:27,681 --> 00:50:28,681
Gong Jeong Han.

763
00:50:29,681 --> 00:50:30,921
It's me, Han Seong Mi.

764
00:50:31,551 --> 00:50:33,651
Your wife is not going to die.

765
00:50:39,561 --> 00:50:40,561
Look at me.

766
00:50:42,261 --> 00:50:45,801
I'll get through my treatment
and be healthy again.

767
00:50:46,271 --> 00:50:47,271
Okay?

768
00:50:54,271 --> 00:50:55,681
Look at you, crying.

769
00:51:01,311 --> 00:51:05,251
- Don't cry.
- Seong Mi, I'll treat you better.

770
00:51:05,251 --> 00:51:07,951
- I promise I'll...
- You'd better mean it.

771
00:51:08,521 --> 00:51:09,521
You have to get better soon.

772
00:51:15,501 --> 00:51:16,731
I'll treat you right, I promise.

773
00:51:26,611 --> 00:51:30,281
Hey, what are you doing?
I told you I'd make breakfast.

774
00:51:30,981 --> 00:51:32,151
You're the one who made breakfast.

775
00:51:33,981 --> 00:51:36,221
I'm heading up,
so just tell them you made it.

776
00:51:37,021 --> 00:51:40,491
I know you're not a morning person,
but I know you wanted to help Mom.

777
00:51:41,451 --> 00:51:45,731
While I'm here, I want to be helpful
to both you and the family.

778
00:51:46,231 --> 00:51:47,231
I'm heading up.

779
00:51:57,841 --> 00:52:01,111
- Hello, CEO Cha.
- Honey, you're too much.

780
00:52:01,371 --> 00:52:02,681
Congratulations
on becoming a business owner.

781
00:52:03,211 --> 00:52:07,011
And huge congratulations to you
on your first day as a star.

782
00:52:07,411 --> 00:52:10,681
Let's finalize everything as soon as
the kids file the paperwork, okay?

783
00:52:10,751 --> 00:52:13,891
Hyun Bin and Eun Bin will handle it
this morning.

784
00:52:14,551 --> 00:52:15,561
Okay.

785
00:52:16,261 --> 00:52:18,831
- How's my "celebrity" look?
- You look amazing.

786
00:52:18,891 --> 00:52:19,891
Think it'll make headlines?

787
00:52:20,791 --> 00:52:23,131
- Let's see your model walk.
- Ta-da!

788
00:52:23,261 --> 00:52:25,471
- Hello.
- Hello, there.

789
00:52:26,171 --> 00:52:27,171
Dad.

790
00:52:27,801 --> 00:52:30,941
You'd better get ready.
Many more people will recognize us,

791
00:52:31,871 --> 00:52:33,171
so you might get tired of it.

792
00:52:35,311 --> 00:52:36,741
Don't be so modest.

793
00:52:38,081 --> 00:52:39,911
Excuse me, are you...
By any chance...

794
00:52:39,981 --> 00:52:44,151
Oh, yes, that's right.
I'm the guy from "Human Theater."

795
00:52:44,881 --> 00:52:46,591
Yang Dong Ik. That's me.

796
00:52:47,691 --> 00:52:50,821
I look better in person, don't I?
Oh, my. Want to get a picture?

797
00:52:50,961 --> 00:52:54,391
- Oh, really? Yes, thank you.
- All right, come stand over here.

798
00:52:54,861 --> 00:52:56,631
Okay, one, two...

799
00:52:59,431 --> 00:53:01,501
No, that's not what I meant.

800
00:53:01,571 --> 00:53:05,371
Could you take my picture with the
Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic?

801
00:53:07,471 --> 00:53:08,471
What the...

802
00:53:09,581 --> 00:53:10,641
My goodness.

803
00:53:11,081 --> 00:53:13,551
Oh, you're
Dr. Gong Jeong Han, aren't you?

804
00:53:13,851 --> 00:53:15,751
Yes, that's right.

805
00:53:17,581 --> 00:53:20,291
Wow, you're so much more handsome
in person.

806
00:53:20,791 --> 00:53:24,791
- You must have seen the show. Yes.
- I really loved the show.

807
00:53:24,861 --> 00:53:26,461
Thank you. Thank you so much.

808
00:53:26,531 --> 00:53:28,861
I'm sorry to bother you,
but could we get a picture together?

809
00:53:28,931 --> 00:53:30,701
- A picture?
- Yes.

810
00:53:30,701 --> 00:53:33,101
- Sure. Give me your phone.
- Excuse me.

811
00:53:33,171 --> 00:53:35,771
- Him?
- No, please take our photo. Please!

812
00:53:35,841 --> 00:53:38,771
- What?
- No, move over a little.

813
00:53:38,841 --> 00:53:40,671
- Okay, all right.
- Right here.

814
00:53:40,741 --> 00:53:43,111
- Okay.
- No, so that my legs look longer,

815
00:53:43,411 --> 00:53:45,011
could you crouch down a bit?
Yes, great.

816
00:53:45,951 --> 00:53:47,751
Oh, okay.

817
00:53:48,111 --> 00:53:49,781
- All right.
- Yes.

818
00:53:49,851 --> 00:53:52,551
Like this? Yes, all right.

819
00:53:52,821 --> 00:53:55,051
- Thank you.
- Sure, of course. You're welcome.

820
00:53:55,121 --> 00:53:56,821
- Thank you.
- We want a picture too!

821
00:53:56,891 --> 00:53:58,931
- Oh, gosh. This is so embarrassing.
- It's okay if you take one, right?

822
00:53:58,931 --> 00:54:01,231
- Oh, yes. Goodness.
- Over here.

823
00:54:01,231 --> 00:54:04,801
- Yes. Okay, sure.
- Take it landscape, please.

824
00:54:05,801 --> 00:54:06,971
I'll just... Whatever.

825
00:54:06,971 --> 00:54:08,531
(Onjeong Market)

826
00:54:11,601 --> 00:54:13,041
("Human Theater," The Onjeong Story)

827
00:54:14,071 --> 00:54:17,911
Unbelievable. Gong Jeong Han's clip
already has 100,000 views,

828
00:54:18,541 --> 00:54:19,751
so why do I only have 20,000?

829
00:54:20,181 --> 00:54:21,411
Is my video really that bad?

830
00:54:25,821 --> 00:54:28,551
Dr. Yang is so fake,
he's hard to watch.

831
00:54:28,891 --> 00:54:31,421
He's more into promoting his clinic
than treating patients.

832
00:54:31,861 --> 00:54:35,261
Dr. Yang, it's so obvious
you're acting for the camera.

833
00:54:35,801 --> 00:54:38,561
Dr. Gong seems to treat
every patient so sincerely.

834
00:54:39,001 --> 00:54:40,071
And the difference is night and day.

835
00:54:40,771 --> 00:54:41,771
Darn it.

836
00:54:42,601 --> 00:54:44,071
Just leave it there.

837
00:54:45,611 --> 00:54:46,941
Everyone's doing well, I hope?

838
00:54:47,141 --> 00:54:51,341
Goodness, our Dr. Gong will get
even more popular at this rate.

839
00:54:51,741 --> 00:54:53,081
All the better for us, right?

840
00:54:53,381 --> 00:54:54,881
It means
the clinic will do even better.

841
00:54:55,281 --> 00:54:58,751
- Exactly.
- Oh, my. You're here!

842
00:54:58,821 --> 00:55:00,691
- Hello.
- Hey, you made it.

843
00:55:01,621 --> 00:55:02,991
Hey, Nurse Oh.

844
00:55:03,361 --> 00:55:05,491
Wow, we've got a lot
of patients today.

845
00:55:05,831 --> 00:55:08,131
Tell me about it. A lot of them came
from really far away, too.

846
00:55:08,431 --> 00:55:09,761
It's so hectic,
I can't even think straight.

847
00:55:11,061 --> 00:55:12,801
Do you think it's because of
"Human Theater?"

848
00:55:13,101 --> 00:55:15,031
- You think so?
- It has to be, right?

849
00:55:15,231 --> 00:55:18,371
Nurse Oh, could you go check
Choi Yong Soon's blood pressure?

850
00:55:18,571 --> 00:55:19,771
Yes, I'm on it.

851
00:55:20,411 --> 00:55:21,511
My gosh.

852
00:55:22,411 --> 00:55:23,411
Oh, boy.

853
00:55:23,511 --> 00:55:27,151
(Reception and Payment)

854
00:55:40,631 --> 00:55:42,001
Wait, there was a witness?

855
00:55:42,401 --> 00:55:46,171
Right, so I made posters using
an AI-generated photo of my father.

856
00:55:46,501 --> 00:55:49,041
When I was putting them up
on the poles...

857
00:55:50,571 --> 00:55:52,111
Someone said
they'd seen him somewhere.

858
00:55:52,911 --> 00:55:55,111
- So when I went to check it out...
- And?

859
00:55:57,011 --> 00:55:58,541
They'd already moved
and no one was there.

860
00:56:00,111 --> 00:56:03,681
But their statement has a clue
about his profession,

861
00:56:03,821 --> 00:56:06,691
so if we start canvassing the area,
we could very well find more clues.

862
00:56:07,921 --> 00:56:09,721
As for filing
a missing person report,

863
00:56:10,261 --> 00:56:13,291
- have you spoken with your family?
- Oh, that...

864
00:56:13,791 --> 00:56:17,001
But the thing is,
my mother is against reporting it.

865
00:56:17,161 --> 00:56:19,201
- I see.
- I see.

866
00:56:19,831 --> 00:56:22,341
Why are you here, then?

867
00:56:22,801 --> 00:56:26,841
Me? I found a cell phone.

868
00:56:27,171 --> 00:56:30,541
So you're here
to turn in a lost item.

869
00:56:30,611 --> 00:56:34,381
You just need to fill out
this found property report.

870
00:56:34,411 --> 00:56:36,721
- All right.
- No, that's not it.

871
00:56:36,951 --> 00:56:39,921
I think I found your phone,
Officer Jung.

872
00:56:40,151 --> 00:56:41,151
What?

873
00:56:41,491 --> 00:56:44,021
Did you leave it somewhere
while you were on patrol?

874
00:56:44,161 --> 00:56:47,331
What? No. My phone's right here.

875
00:56:47,591 --> 00:56:50,561
What? So it is. Then...

876
00:56:51,101 --> 00:56:53,631
Whose phone could this be?

877
00:56:54,301 --> 00:56:55,601
Yes, I wonder.

878
00:56:58,141 --> 00:56:59,141
What?

879
00:56:59,771 --> 00:57:01,941
What the...
Why is my picture on here?

880
00:57:02,711 --> 00:57:05,411
What? What's this...

881
00:57:05,981 --> 00:57:07,411
Oh, Mr. Gong.

882
00:57:09,551 --> 00:57:11,251
- It's pink.
- What?

883
00:57:11,251 --> 00:57:14,921
- The phone is pink.
- Where could he have found this?

884
00:57:20,061 --> 00:57:24,131
- Hey, what are you looking for?
- My phone.

885
00:57:24,631 --> 00:57:26,931
I'm sure I left it on the desk,
but now it's gone.

886
00:57:27,271 --> 00:57:30,771
Really? The desk?
Hey, was that your phone?

887
00:57:30,941 --> 00:57:34,111
I thought someone left it behind,
so I took it to the police station.

888
00:57:34,341 --> 00:57:35,341
You, what?

889
00:57:35,881 --> 00:57:39,981
Oh, come on!
Why would you take it there?

890
00:57:39,981 --> 00:57:41,981
Oh, shoot. It slipped my mind.
I had no idea.

891
00:57:42,421 --> 00:57:44,751
Go on, I just dropped it off. Hurry!

892
00:57:44,821 --> 00:57:48,221
- Gosh, this is bad!
- Relax. Hey, hurry up.

893
00:57:48,221 --> 00:57:51,791
Hurry, run!

894
00:57:51,921 --> 00:57:53,961
All right. Success.

895
00:57:55,631 --> 00:57:56,631
Unbelievable.

896
00:57:56,701 --> 00:57:58,131
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

897
00:57:58,201 --> 00:57:59,201
(Police)

898
00:58:00,531 --> 00:58:01,531
Oh, well...

899
00:58:03,501 --> 00:58:06,371
I'm here to return your lost item.

900
00:58:09,811 --> 00:58:11,541
(Oh Jin Ah)

901
00:58:15,051 --> 00:58:16,821
(Police)

902
00:58:24,161 --> 00:58:26,561
(Taehan)

903
00:58:27,931 --> 00:58:30,261
What's the emergency?

904
00:58:31,301 --> 00:58:33,871
We've hit a snag with your contract,
Pacu Nacho.

905
00:58:34,901 --> 00:58:36,141
Is Director Baek opposing it?

906
00:58:37,701 --> 00:58:38,871
But why?

907
00:58:39,211 --> 00:58:41,171
He's saying your skills
haven't been proven yet.

908
00:58:42,511 --> 00:58:43,581
What does that even mean?

909
00:58:44,081 --> 00:58:45,141
He proved himself with the launch
at Hyegyeong Department Store,

910
00:58:45,141 --> 00:58:46,381
and the event was a success too.

911
00:58:46,511 --> 00:58:50,181
He even brought in major buyers.
What more proof does he need?

912
00:58:50,421 --> 00:58:53,751
Director Baek just doesn't want me
staying at Taehan.

913
00:58:53,951 --> 00:58:54,951
No, it's not about that.

914
00:58:55,591 --> 00:58:57,391
He wants to clip my wings.

915
00:58:58,121 --> 00:59:01,061
That way, it'll be easier to oust me
when my father is gone.

916
00:59:02,761 --> 00:59:05,161
Then when his one-year contract
is up,

917
00:59:05,731 --> 00:59:07,101
he could actually be fired?

918
00:59:07,431 --> 00:59:08,871
There's a very strong possibility.

919
00:59:09,471 --> 00:59:10,501
That...

920
00:59:11,241 --> 00:59:13,571
will be decided by the results
of the upcoming fashion show.

921
00:59:14,841 --> 00:59:17,181
If we land global orders
and show strong results,

922
00:59:17,541 --> 00:59:18,711
I'll get my way.

923
00:59:21,511 --> 00:59:24,121
That's a ton of pressure
on Ms. Gong.

924
00:59:24,421 --> 00:59:25,821
Tell me about it.

925
00:59:27,421 --> 00:59:28,791
Listen, about this...

926
00:59:29,361 --> 00:59:31,121
Let's keep this from Ms. Gong.

927
00:59:31,891 --> 00:59:34,691
Of course.
She's got enough on her plate.

928
00:59:36,931 --> 00:59:39,201
Is there something else
she's dealing with?

929
00:59:41,071 --> 00:59:42,071
No.

930
00:59:42,641 --> 00:59:43,641
There's nothing.

931
00:59:44,841 --> 00:59:45,841
Nothing at all.

932
00:59:57,821 --> 00:59:59,421
(My Woo Jae)

933
01:00:06,791 --> 01:00:08,061
(My Woo Jae)

934
01:00:14,371 --> 01:00:15,871
Are you avoiding my calls?

935
01:00:17,671 --> 01:00:20,011
Hold on, I'll get Min Seo.

936
01:00:20,571 --> 01:00:21,571
Eun Bin.

937
01:00:23,111 --> 01:00:24,511
I came here to see you.

938
01:00:25,241 --> 01:00:26,411
Me? Why?

939
01:00:27,081 --> 01:00:28,681
Because I had a feeling
something was wrong.

940
01:00:29,621 --> 01:00:32,851
What makes you think
something's wrong?

941
01:00:33,721 --> 01:00:35,291
Because you've never acted
like this before.

942
01:00:37,021 --> 01:00:39,361
You've never gone a day
without seeing me.

943
01:00:39,861 --> 01:00:41,531
You'd either come visit me
every day,

944
01:00:42,031 --> 01:00:43,261
or on the days we couldn't meet,

945
01:00:43,601 --> 01:00:46,201
you'd always video-call me
just so I could see your face.

946
01:00:50,101 --> 01:00:51,441
You're not sick or anything,
are you?

947
01:01:01,781 --> 01:01:02,881
Here.

948
01:01:07,721 --> 01:01:08,721
Open it.

949
01:01:09,721 --> 01:01:12,361
I bought it for you
with my first paycheck.

950
01:01:23,371 --> 01:01:24,401
It's so pretty.

951
01:01:25,401 --> 01:01:26,971
So it was for me.

952
01:01:28,241 --> 01:01:31,411
I wasn't sure what you'd like,
so Min Seo helped me pick it out.

953
01:01:32,551 --> 01:01:33,881
I see.

954
01:01:37,821 --> 01:01:38,821
Here.

955
01:01:40,721 --> 01:01:41,991
I'm just glad I got to see you.

956
01:01:42,791 --> 01:01:43,791
I'll get going.

957
01:01:47,231 --> 01:01:48,391
Eun Bin.

958
01:01:49,701 --> 01:01:51,401
If you're ever going through
something,

959
01:01:52,161 --> 01:01:53,271
you can talk to me.

960
01:01:54,731 --> 01:01:55,741
Why?

961
01:01:57,141 --> 01:01:59,541
Because you were always there for me
when I was having a hard time.

962
01:02:00,911 --> 01:02:03,341
I feel like it's only right
for me to do the same for you.

963
01:02:07,011 --> 01:02:08,011
I'll be going.

964
01:02:35,511 --> 01:02:37,911
- Hey.
- Why didn't you tell me?

965
01:02:38,541 --> 01:02:39,551
Tell you what?

966
01:02:39,651 --> 01:02:42,521
Why didn't you tell me you went
with Woo Jae to pick out my gift?

967
01:02:43,821 --> 01:02:46,891
How could I?
It was supposed to be a surprise.

968
01:02:47,851 --> 01:02:48,851
I...

969
01:02:49,491 --> 01:02:52,061
I thought you came here
to take everything from me.

970
01:02:52,731 --> 01:02:53,731
What?

971
01:02:53,731 --> 01:02:55,131
That you approached me
knowing everything...

972
01:02:55,731 --> 01:02:58,501
to take away everything I hold dear.

973
01:02:59,471 --> 01:03:01,601
What are you talking about?

974
01:03:02,571 --> 01:03:05,101
Did you misunderstand things
between Woo Jae and me?

975
01:03:06,271 --> 01:03:07,271
Yes.

976
01:03:07,771 --> 01:03:08,811
I did.

977
01:03:09,781 --> 01:03:11,411
I'm so sorry.

978
01:03:11,781 --> 01:03:14,111
If you want me to,
I'll leave tomorrow.

979
01:03:15,051 --> 01:03:17,381
I hate seeing you this upset
because of me.

980
01:03:18,421 --> 01:03:20,391
- You'd really do that?
- Yes.

981
01:03:20,391 --> 01:03:23,561
No, I mean... If you found out
where your birth mother was,

982
01:03:25,021 --> 01:03:27,731
could you really just watch her
from afar?

983
01:03:29,461 --> 01:03:31,561
- Why?
- I'm asking, could you?

984
01:03:33,201 --> 01:03:34,201
Yes.

985
01:03:35,871 --> 01:03:37,671
I know where your birth mother is,

986
01:03:38,801 --> 01:03:39,871
and I'll tell you.

987
01:03:42,781 --> 01:03:44,241
(3H Acupressure Bed)

988
01:03:44,311 --> 01:03:49,151
Honey, you sent me flowers?

989
01:03:51,121 --> 01:03:53,321
Yes, I'll do a great job.

990
01:03:53,921 --> 01:03:55,121
I'll see you at home later.

991
01:03:56,261 --> 01:03:57,761
I'm so happy.

992
01:03:59,361 --> 01:04:02,131
You have to keep your promise, okay?

993
01:04:03,101 --> 01:04:04,101
I will.

994
01:04:21,011 --> 01:04:22,011
Eun Bin.

995
01:04:22,821 --> 01:04:26,021
If this gets out, my mom will be
kicked out of the house.

996
01:04:33,261 --> 01:04:36,001
(3H Acupressure Bed)

997
01:04:36,061 --> 01:04:37,201
Where should I put these?

998
01:04:37,361 --> 01:04:39,571
(3H Acupressure Bed)

999
01:05:32,351 --> 01:05:35,351
(Recipe For Love)

1000
01:05:35,421 --> 01:05:38,891
Could you call 911?
I think my heart's on fire.

1001
01:05:41,831 --> 01:05:44,161
I went to the hospital today.

1002
01:05:46,401 --> 01:05:47,901
I'm sorry, Min Seo.

1003
01:05:48,801 --> 01:05:52,611
I called her "Mother" not knowing
she was my real mom.

1004
01:05:56,011 --> 01:05:57,381
What? Who is it?

1005
01:05:57,881 --> 01:05:59,011
It's my father.

1006
01:06:00,338 --> 01:06:02,138
Dramaday.me
